The Entrepreneurship and Innovation programme is intended to serve entrepreneurs and companies to raise funds for innovative entrepreneurship.
Companies should raise funds for the introduction of new technologies, for industrial research, but also for the introduction of more effective organizational methods.
The Czech Republic has so far been one of the least successful countries in drawing money from EU funds.
