The driver’s license could not be changed by 600,000 people.
Six hundred thousand drivers missed the deadline and failed to exchange their old driver's license, which expires at the end of the year.
Today is the last day people can apply for a replacement so that the authorities can issue a new card before the end of the year.
However, the ministry is not afraid that hundreds of thousands of drivers would be put on the road after the New Year without a valid license.
According to the authorities, the card was not exchanged mainly by those who do not want to drive anymore.
While municipalities are reporting a sharp decline in interest in changing their driver's license, authorities in the capital are overwhelmed by requests and interest in changing their license has increased this week.
The city handles about 2000 clients a day.
We waited in the queues for about half an hour.
About 140,000 drivers have not yet exchanged their driving licences in Prague.
It takes 20 days to issue a new card.
However, it is possible to apply for extradition within a shortened period of five days.
In this case, the driver will pay five hundred crowns.
Motorists who fail to change their licence by the end of the year and drive on the road without a valid driver’s license will face a fine from January.
The offender will pay a maximum of two thousand crowns.
The police officer can also deal with the offence by agreement.
In the event of an administrative offence, the fine will amount to CZK 2,500.
According to previous information, even a person who is not going anywhere could be fined by the town hall.
