Ninety percent
Afghan insurgent activity is at its highest in five years, according to U.S. military data.
The number of violent attacks increased by 27 percent compared to the previous year, while in the southern province of Helmand it increased by 60 percent.
NATO countries have about 40,000 troops in Afghanistan, about a quarter of them in the southern territory.
According to the United States, however, the Allies have reached the very limit in the organization and equipment of the troops.
Specifically, they are asking for more helicopters, soldiers and experts for training Afghan troops.
"We're going to have to think seriously about specific targets for the coming time and how to achieve them," Gates said.
NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop also spoke today.
“I’m not happy with what we have on the ground and in the air in Afghanistan.
