After the class votes, 20 of the 23 children choose Mohamed as their favorite name.
Of course Muhammad is the name of a Muslim prophet, but most of all it is a very common first name in Sudan.
The children then created a book for their class with a photo of a teddy bear accompanied by a caption: "My name is Muhammad".
The teddy bear itself had no label with the name on it, but the trouble is in the very depiction of the prophet considered an insult to Islam.
