Decision for the status quo
Sunday’s election will be held without any expectation: the Russians will vote for President Putin’s party, United Russia.
Affirming thus, after the end of the very little free election campaign, their preoccupation with stability, indeed with authoritarianism.
Today, three days before the elections to the Chamber of Deputies, Russian President Vladimir Putin will give voters a pre-recorded television message on public television, but the content of which is kept secret.
He does so from the position of the leader of United Russia, a pro-Kremlin party that seems to celebrate a landslide victory.
