Which insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which protects the driver in the event of an accident, represents a significant expense, which depends on various factors, such as age, condition, gender, length of driving licence, type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This liability takes the form of an insurance contract, which provides that the insurance company receives an agreed insurance sum of a certain amount for taking charge of the payment of damages in the event of an insured event.
The premium is the price of insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors, such as age, status, gender, length of possession of a driving licence, the type of vehicle being insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the more likely an accident is to occur, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both 25-year-olds and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, based on checks, insurance companies have concluded that married people have fewer crashes than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of trips and thus the likelihood of having an accident.
Increasing the frequency of trips increases the likelihood.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when setting the premium price.
Therefore, the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the insurance that best fits his profile as an insured person.
We will show here the most important variables for choosing this or that type of insurance, which, in addition to meeting the type of insured, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of twenty-five face various disadvantages such as low driving experience and short possession of a driver’s license when they want to take out premiums at an affordable price.
Although insurance against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all risks with a discount of premiums so that they get insurance coverage for all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would assume the client’s participation in the settlement of the insured event.
"The part of the claim settlement provided by the client will be pre-determined when determining the premium price, which will be the higher the lower the deductible," explains Luis Noguera, Head of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is insurance extended to other traffic participants so that the client insures against damages caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, it would be insured against theft, fire and loss of vehicle.
Recommendations.
If you are under 25 years of age, try to be attentive and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce insurance premiums in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that an insurance company has.
Malus, on the other hand, is the increase in the above-mentioned base rate.
"Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company has had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus,” explains Noguera.
After crossing the threshold of twenty-five years, drivers have it easier when they go to take out insurance, as their client risk index decreases, thanks to their experience.
For this reason, it is most recommended to take out insurance against all risks at a discount.
“Young people are usually unable to take advantage of the experience they have gained in the event of an accident, and even in driving,” the director of a European company in Spain said, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, when the “newcomer’s fear” has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but does not have children yet, it is better to take out insurance against all risks, if his economic situation allows it.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies to have the lowest risk index and therefore their premiums will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks at a premium discount (which could amount to 300 euros) or at a high bonus, the insurance extended to other traffic participants, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
“Their proceedings are calmer and their purchasing power is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount,” Luis Noguera points out.
Pensioners are recommended insurance against all risks with a discount on insurance (which is 150 euros) or insurance extended to other participants of the operation, if a high bonus has been achieved.
It must be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in the event of a crash, but also because it represents a considerable expense, which is a good reason to study the insurance options that would suit us best given our personal situation.
