The report of the President of the Supreme Audit Office says, among other recommendations, that the commissions should be guided by the guidelines of the Criminal Records Bureau, which helps employers with checks in several countries.
"Although we found that part of the personnel records contained evidence of these controls, they are not being conducted regularly," the report said.
