However, during the trial before U.S. District Judge Ewing Werlein Jr., each confessed to one fraud.
The case of the three former executives of Greenwich NatWest, a unit of Royal Bank of Scotland Group PLC, has been featured on the front pages for the entire two years of the extradition proceedings.
In the United States, their case is one of the unclosed parts of an investigation launched after the 2001 Enron crash.
