England must decide: Owais Shah or Ravi Bopara?
We have two dilemmas, one almost as difficult as the other.
Who's going to be number six for England this weekend in Kandy, Owais Shah, or Ravi Bopara?
And, in a broader context, no less relevant than the first Test against Sri Lanka, who is to make that decision?
The second question is relevant because David Graveney, chairman of the selection committee, who holds this position at best on borrowed time, has Peter Moores, head coach, and Michael Vaughan, captain, making the decision to help, and because the table of Hugh Morris, head manager of the English team, begins to fill up with applications for the position of national selector, if not necessarily full-time.
