It is not easy to find what gets one to the top of his profession, while someone else never gets past the lower level, sometimes because of a lack of luck rather than ability.
It is not only in cricket that the choice is demanding and requires a review, which in the end always has to be subjective.
Is this the right time for Bopara to move up?
Is that fair to Shah, if so?
We could ask the same question in another area, say here: John Edwards or "Tubby" Banerjee, both smart young executives with a good education and insight in the field, should be promoted to the committee - the place is only for one.
