In order for children to start learning as soon as possible, the last year of kindergarten is free - a model that is also taken over by other federal states.
If students’ performance improves significantly, future comparative studies will show.
When the Pisa study was carried out in 2003, the proportion of high-risk pupils decreased from 29 to 20%.
Overall, however, Saarland has not improved as much as other federal states.
Beavers are better at counting.
And to the disappointment of the Saar Studies of Pisa, they do not compare knowledge of foreign languages - otherwise Saarland could score points in this area.
